Class B2DJoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • box2d.B2DJoint

  • public class B2DJoint
extends java.lang.Object
    The B2DJoint class is comparable to a position vector with B2DBone connected to it. It has a mutation() code implemented.

    • Constructor Detail

      • B2DJoint

        public B2DJoint(float[] minXY_maxXY,
                int id_in)
        Creates a new B2DJoint within the given bounds minXY_maxXY randomly.

        The coordinates are given as follows: [left, bottom, right, top]

        Parameters:
        minXY_maxXY - bounding box, wherein the new B2DJoint will be created.
        id_in - gives this instance a final ID.
